{heading:Movement}

{#--text-color-faded:Directional movement:} {Bindings:GameMoveUp} (up), {Bindings:GameMoveLeft} (left), {Bindings:GameMoveDown} (down), {Bindings:GameMoveRight} (right)

{#--text-color-faded:Move towards mouse:} {Bindings:GameMoveDirection}

{#--text-color-faded:Move t' th' tile under th' mouse:} {Bindings:GameMoveToTile}

{#--text-color-faded:Skip/pass a turn:} {Bindings:GameIdle} or {Bindings:GameMoveDirection} (with yer mouse over yer character).

{#--text-color-faded:Facin' a direction without movin':} {Bindings:GameFaceDirection} and yer character will face towards yer mouse (thar be correspondin' facin' binds fer all directions as well).

If thar be too much or too little delay between turnin' a direction and movin', ye can fine-tune it in th' {link(Menu.Options.3):Options Menu}.

{heading:Actions}

Interactin' through th' world be done mostly through th' {link(Menu.HelpArticle.Actions):actions} menu, opened usin' {Bindings:GameActions}.

{heading:Usin' Items}

See {link(Menu.HelpArticle.Actions):Actions} and {link(Menu.HelpArticle.Quickslots):Quickslots}.

{heading:Item Management}

__Droppin' items__

{#--text-color-faded:Drop an item:} {Bindings:GameItemDrop} (when th' mouse be over th' item), or use th' {link(Menu.HelpArticle.Actions):"Drop" action} on th' item. 

{#--text-color-faded:Drop all o' a type o' item:} {Bindings:GameItemDropAll} (when th' mouse be over th' type o' item t' drop), or use th' {link(Menu.HelpArticle.Actions):"Drop All" action}.

If thar be a tile in th' way o' droppin' an item, by default nothin' will happen. Ye may change this functionality in th' "Drop Location" settin', available in th' {link(Menu.Options.3):Options Menu} and th' Quick Settings dialog.

__Movin' items__

{#--text-color-faded:Quickly movin' items between containers:} {Bindings:GameItemQuickMove} (when th' mouse be over th' item)

{#--text-color-faded:Quickly movin' all o' th' same type o' item between containers:} {Bindings:GameItemQuickMoveAll} (when th' mouse be over th' type o' item)

Quick-movin' items works with yer open container dialog, or, if thar be no container dialog open, th' container yer character be facin'.

{heading:More Information}

Hoverin' over elements on screen will typically reveal more information, usually in a tooltip. Some examples include items in dialogs, and doodads, creatures, and items in th' world. Items in th' craftin' dialog will highlight th' items that will be used when they be crafted.

Tooltips fer tiles in th' world can be disabled. When this be th' case, ye can still get information about th' tile ye be hoverin' over with {Bindings:GameInspect}.

quickslots:
{link(Menu.HelpArticle.Actions):Openin' an item's menu t' perform actions} can be tiresome. Quickslots be fer usin' an action on an item with th' press o' a bind.

{heading:Quickslottin' an Item}

Ye can drag some godforsaken item into one o' yer nine quickslots t' quickslot th' item in that slot. Ye can also use any o' th' quickslot binds t' toggle th' item bein' quickslotted t' th' slot o' th' bind ye press. Alternatively, ye can use th' {link(Menu.HelpArticle.Actions):"Add t' Quickslot" action} t' add it t' an open quickslot.

{heading:Usin' a Quickslotted Item}

By default, pressin' th' bind fer a quickslot will perform th' default {link(Menu.HelpArticle.Actions):action} fer th' item in that slot; th' action depends on what kind o' item it is. 

Ye can change th' action t' perform fer a quickslot item by openin' th' actions menu ({Bindings:GameItemMenu}), and clickin' th' x icon next t' th' preferred action, turnin' it into a √.

{heading:Removin' a Quickslotted Item}

Thar be two binds provided fer removin' items from quickslots. Ye can press {Bindings:GameQuickSlotClear} t' clear th' hovered item from its quickslot, or t' clear th' hovered quickslot. Ye can also press any o' th' quickslot binds t' toggle th' hovered item bein' quickslotted t' that slot.
